"""
Golden CCR-IRB-1 scenario: single 5-year GBP vanilla IR swap, unmargined,
IRB-permissioned corporate counterparty (F-IRB, CRR Art. 153(1)).

Pipeline position:
    fixture-builder output -> test-writer (tests/acceptance/ccr/test_ccr_irb1.py)
    -> engine-implementer (engine/ccr/pipeline_adapter.py model_id enrichment)

Scenario design (P8.31 / CCR-IRB-1):
    One trade (T_IRB_001): 5-year GBP vanilla IR swap, notional GBP 100m,
    MtM = 0.0 (at-par), delta = 1.0 (non-option directional long).
    One netting set (NS_IRB_001): counterparty CP_IRB_001, legally enforceable
    (Art. 295 condition met), unmargined.
    Zero margin agreements: no CSA in place.
    Zero CCR collateral: no posted or received collateral.

Counterparty design:
    CP_IRB_001: entity_type="corporate", country_code="GB", non-SME.
    A matching internal rating row carries pd=0.0150 and model_id="MOD_CORP_FIRB"
    so that the hierarchy pipeline promotes them to internal_pd=0.0150 and
    internal_model_id="MOD_CORP_FIRB" on the counterparty_lookup frame.

    The classifier resolves approach_applied=foundation_irb for the CCR-derived
    synthetic row once engine/ccr/pipeline_adapter.py is fixed to carry model_id
    through to the synthetic exposure row (the load-bearing gap documented in the
    P8.31 proposal).  Until that engine fix lands, approach_applied falls back to
    standardised; the fixture still supplies all the data.

Model permission:
    MOD_CORP_FIRB → exposure_class="corporate", approach="foundation_irb", GB.
    This row must be added to the model_permissions fixture (see
    tests/fixtures/model_permissions/model_permissions.py) or provided inline
    as model_permissions on a ResolvedHierarchyBundle.  This file adds it to
    the shared model_permissions.parquet via
    ``create_ccr_irb1_model_permission()``.

SA-CCR EAD hand-calc (for cross-check; GOLDEN MUST BE GENERATED by pipeline):
    SF_IR = 0.005; supervisory_delta = 1.0; MF_unmargined = sqrt(min(5,1)/1) = 1.0
    Supervisory duration SD(S=0, E=5) = (exp(-0.05×0)−exp(-0.05×5)) / 0.05 ≈ 4.323
    Adjusted notional = 100_000_000 × 4.323 ≈ 432_332_358
    Effective notional (EN) = 432_332_358 × 1.0 × 1.0 (delta × MF) = 432_332_358
    Add-on_IR = 0.005 × 432_332_358 ≈ 2_161_662
    RC = max(0 − 0, 0) = 0
    EAD_ccr = 1.4 × (0 + 2_161_662) ≈ 3_026_327
    Note: exact value generated by pipeline run; 5-year swap < CCR-A1 10-year swap
    (CCR-A1 ead_ccr ≈ 5_480_018 with supervisory duration for 10-year tenor).

IRB K hand-calc (CRR Art. 153(1), for cross-check; GOLDEN MUST BE GENERATED):
    PD = max(0.0150, 0.0003) = 0.0150; LGD = 0.45 (Art. 161(1)(a) F-IRB senior
    unsecured); M = clip(5.0, 1, 5) = 5.0
    R ≈ 0.12 × (1 − exp(−50×0.0150)) / (1 − exp(−50))
        + 0.24 × [1 − (1 − exp(−50×0.0150)) / (1 − exp(−50))]
      ≈ 0.12 × 0.527 + 0.24 × 0.473 ≈ 0.176568
    b = (0.11852 − 0.05478 × ln(0.0150))^2 ≈ 0.121508
    MA = (1 + (M − 2.5) × b) / (1 − 1.5 × b) ≈ 1.594607
    K = (LGD × N((N⁻¹(PD) + sqrt(R) × N⁻¹(0.999)) / sqrt(1 − R)) − LGD × PD) × MA
      ≈ 0.069095 (scaling factor 1.06 already included in K formula — see CRR)
    risk_weight = K × 12.5 ≈ 145.99% (includes 1.06 scaling)
    RWA = risk_weight × EAD_ccr (generated)

Expected output assertions for test-writer (exposure_reference = "ccr__NS_IRB_001"):
    risk_type = CCR_DERIVATIVE
    source_netting_set_id = NS_IRB_001
    ccr_method = sa_ccr
    ead_ccr = generated (< 5_480_018 — 5-year < 10-year)
    ead_final == ead_ccr  (no CRM; load-bearing identity)
    exposure_class = corporate
    approach_applied = foundation_irb  (LOAD-BEARING — requires P8.31 engine fix)
    pd / pd_floored ≈ 0.0150
    lgd / lgd_floored = 0.45
    irb_maturity_m = 5.0
    k ≈ 0.069095 (generated — polars-normal-stats may differ in last ulp)
    risk_weight ≈ 1.459913  (generated)
    rwa_final = risk_weight × ead_ccr  (generated)

Golden file note:
    ead_ccr, k, risk_weight, and rwa_final are NOT hand-typed constants in this
    fixture.  The test-writer must generate the golden JSON by running the full
    CRR pipeline over the bundle returned by ``build_raw_data_bundle_ccr_irb1()``
    and writing the result to tests/expected_outputs/ccr/CCR-IRB-1.json using
    the same generation pattern as CCR-A1.  This file supplies only the
    structural data; golden generation belongs to the test layer.

References:
    - CRR Art. 153(1) (IRB K formula for corporate)
    - CRR Art. 161(1)(a) (F-IRB senior unsecured LGD = 45%)
    - CRR Art. 162(2)(b) (non-IMM maturity: weighted-average remaining, 1y–5y clip)
    - CRR Art. 163 (PD floor 0.03%)
    - CRR Art. 274(2) (SA-CCR EAD = α·(RC + PFE))
    - CRR Art. 279b (PFE add-on — interest rate asset class)
    - CRR Art. 295 (contractual netting recognition)
    - src/rwa_calc/data/schemas.py — TRADE_SCHEMA, NETTING_SET_SCHEMA,
      COUNTERPARTY_SCHEMA, RATINGS_SCHEMA, MODEL_PERMISSIONS_SCHEMA
"""

